00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:00,871
Break outta your cage, Pikul.

258
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,636
Break out now.

259
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,791
(Explosive hiss)
Unh!

260
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:12,156
(Groaning)

261
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:18,117
The swelling doesn't last long.

262
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:21,312
Tomorrow, you won't even notice it.

263
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,789
(Moaning) I love it.

264
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,677
Great.

265
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,914
What's going on?!
I can't move my legs!

266
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:36,276
The procedure comes
with its own epidural.

267
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:38,709
Just like when you have a baby.

268
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:42,156
Kinda like instant paralysis
from the waist down.

269
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,912
That's why it didn't hurt.

270
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,673
It'll wear off in no time.

271
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,749
I'm gonna go wash up.

272
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:53,997
You two, make yourselves at home.

273
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:07,596
You don't have to wait
for the swelling to go down.

274
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:18,230
You're gonna port into me...
while I'm paralysed?

275
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:22,919
You wanted to play my game,
didn't you?

276
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,389
Yeah, I did. I do, but...

277
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:27,431
Here? Now?

278
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,909
It's an instant-on world, isn't it?

279
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:36,075
What's that for? Feels... cold.

280
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:40,153
New ports are sometimes a bit tight.

281
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,872
Wouldn't wanna hurt ya.

282
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:47,749
How come...

283
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:50,952
bio-ports don't get infected?

284
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,877
I mean,

285
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:56,829
they open right into your body.

286
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,637
Listen to what
you're saying, Pikul.

287
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:03,557
Don't be ludicrous.

288
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:17,874
Don't you think
you could call me Ted?

289
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:20,838
Maybe afterwards.

290
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,155
Shit!

291
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:55,073
Pikul! I can't believe it.

292
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,479
You blew my pod!

293
00:27:57,760 --> 00:28:00,149
- You must have neural-surged!
- What?

294
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:04,711
I jacked you in and you panicked.
Now it's totally fucked!

295
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:07,438
This is a disaster.

296
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,512
I was nervous, but I didn't panic.

297
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:15,799
I was forced to trust you and you
panicked and you neural-surged

298
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:17,677
and you blew my pod.

299
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:20,320
You can get a new pod.

300
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,429
Pikul,

301
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:27,917
in this pod is the only,

302
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,355
the original version of eXistenZ,

303
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:34,149
an entire game system
that cost 38 million to develop,

304
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,549
not including pre-release
marketing costs,

305
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:39,916
and I'm locked outside my own game.

306
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,560
I can't get me in or it out!

307
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:45,035
Are you serious?

308
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:47,793
That's the only version that exists?

309
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:52,874
It's the only one and it's stuck
inside and it's your fault.

310
00:28:57,880 --> 00:29:02,158
I've devoted five passionate years
to this strange little creature.

311
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:08,949
And I've never regretted it, Pikul,

312
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:13,232
'cause it was the only thing
that could give my life any meaning.

313
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:14,958
Allegra,

314
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,837
why is it my fault?

315
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,717
I'm telling you I didn't...

316
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:23,519
I did not neural-surge. I didn't.

317
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:25,477
I didn't feel any surging.

318
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:28,596
(Gas) It's not your fault.

319
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,750
It's my fault.

320
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,829
Oh, no, Gas. Not you.

321
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:38,509
I wouldn't try to use
that bio-port again.

322
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:41,996
'Cept maybe
for a toaster or somethin'.

323
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:45,037
What's going on?

324
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:50,029
You're worth a lot of money...
if you're dead.

325
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:53,317
- What are you talking about?
- You know what.

326
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:57,911
It's all over the countryside.
$5 million for her dead body.

327
00:29:58,040 --> 00:29:59,917
No questions asked.

328
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:05,474
But, she changed your life.

329
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:08,870
Yep. And now I'm gonna change hers.

330
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:13,751
Wait! Why did you install
a bad port into me?

331
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:18,351
There's a big bonus for killing
Allegra Geller's latest game

332
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:21,040
or whatever it is.

333
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:23,588
I think I just did that, didn't I?

334
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:30,269
But can you kill me, Gas?
Can you kill a person?

335
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:34,148
Can you do that?

336
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:36,396
Hide my body?

337
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:39,080
Contact the crazies?

338
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:41,191
Trust them to pay up?

339
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:45,353
Hand over my now decaying,
fucking grotesque corpse?

340
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:48,358
Really expect them to
hand over five mil cash?

341
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:52,638
Don't you ever go
to the fucking movies?

342
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,630
I like your script.

343
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:01,390
I wanna be in it.

344
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:05,231
(Explosive hiss)

345
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,952
(Hissing)

346
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:29,110
Oh, God, I think he's dead.

347
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:35,272
- He wanted to kill you.
- Yep.

348
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,598
That's two people in one day...

349
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,636
who wanted to actually kill you.

350
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:48,996
I've never been more popular.

351
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,991
Allegra, we need help.

352
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:56,150
You're right.
I've gotta get this pod fixed.

353
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,797
(Pikul) We're going skiing?

354
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:32,592
(Squealing)

355
00:32:34,320 --> 00:32:36,834
Hey. Hey.

356
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:39,190
Look at that huge bug.

357
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:42,031
It's got two heads.

358
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:45,032
It's not a bug.
It's a mutated amphibian.

359
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:48,869
It's a frog-salamander-lizard thing.

360
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:51,076
Sign of the times.

361
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:02,513
What happens if somebody
here wants to ski?

362
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:07,316
Come on, Pikul. Nobody actually
skis anymore. You know that.

363
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:22,595
No, don't use that!
And bring me the sterile wash.

364
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:24,517
(Knocking)

365
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:29,639
My darling.

366
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:38,190
Allegra Geller.

367
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:44,752
I'm so pleased and...
s-so astonished to see you here.

368
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:50,358
- Kiri Vinokur, Ted Pikul.
- Hello.

369
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:53,476
Sterile wash.

370
00:33:55,080 --> 00:33:57,310
Um, I hear this ridiculous story

371
00:33:57,400 --> 00:34:00,198
about some fatwa against you.

372
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:03,590
The company are desperately
trying to find you.

373
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:06,240
Is this really serious?
Are you in danger?

374
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:09,676
There have been a couple
of attempts on my life.

375
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:10,835
This is unbearable.

376
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:14,913
The company must stop this.
They owe you protection.

377
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,230
But I don't know
if they can do anything.

378
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:19,276
It's open season on me.

379
00:34:20,720 --> 00:34:23,837
Well, you will be safe here.
I assure you.

380
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:27,595
I will contact Antenna right away
and have them come to collect you.

381
00:34:27,720 --> 00:34:31,110
No, Kiri, don't. You mustn't
let anybody know that we're here.

382
00:34:31,200 --> 00:34:34,795
I can't be sure that Antenna
is completely safe for me.

383
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,199
(Kiri) I understand. Yes.

384
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:38,475
You know,

385
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:43,231
you can hide out
in one of the guest chalets

386
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:45,191
as long as you like.

387
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:49,078
And I'll make sure
you get fresh towels.

388
00:34:50,640 --> 00:34:53,473
And make sure I don't lose
everything in here.

389
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:57,317
You bet.

390
00:35:01,560 --> 00:35:03,835
(Kiri speaking foreign language)

391
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:10,155
Take that.

392
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:12,759
Good.

393
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,437
Pull this back.

394
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:24,239
- What did you port into?
- Pikul's bio-port.

395
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,995
Really? That's what caused
all the damage.

396
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:31,517
It was, uh,
a flawed installation. My first.

397
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:34,159
(Kiri) Well...

398
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:39,360
it fried a lot
of very expensive neural webbing.

399
00:35:39,440 --> 00:35:42,113
- You see?
- Looks like an animal.

400
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:47,037
Feels like you're operating
on somebody's pet dog.

401
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:52,592
I told you, Landry, we have
become glorified veterinarians.

402
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:56,234
Put a little in there, please.

403
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:03,310
The eXistenZ game-pod
is basically an animal, Mr Pikul.

404
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:06,790
It's grown from fertilised
amphibian eggs

405
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:09,354
stuffed with synthetic DNA.

406
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:12,670
Only Antenna Research has this.

407
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:15,633
Wow. Where do the batteries go?

408
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:18,717
Very funny.

409
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:23,909
He's not kidding.
He's a total PR nerd.

410
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,468
It ports into you.
You're the power source.

411
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:30,473
Your body, your nervous system,
your metabolism, your energy.

412
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:33,990
You get tired, run down,
it won't run properly.

413
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,389
(Kiri) OK.

414
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:39,199
Landry here
will finish up the pod work.

415
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:43,478
Now, let's, uh, get that
nasty bio-port out of you,

416
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:45,272
put a fresh one in.

417
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:53,990
Oww! It hurts.

418
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,196
I think it's infected.

419
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:58,271
No. It's not infected.

420
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:02,280
It's just excited.

421
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:05,390
It wants action.

422
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:08,233
But I don't want action -
me, I mean -

423
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:11,118
the bearer of the excited bio-port.

424
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:18,108
My baby here has now taken
three major hits, Pikul.

425
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:22,074
In the church, in the gas
station and on the operating table.

426
00:37:22,160 --> 00:37:25,994
The only way I can tell
if everything's OK...

427
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:29,954
is to play eXistenZ
with somebody friendly.

428
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:33,949
Are you friendly,

429
00:37:34,040 --> 00:37:36,270
or are you not?

430
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:43,190
You're telling me this thing
will run off my body's energy?

431
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:45,157
That's how they work.

432
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:50,278
See?
You're hummin' along already.

433
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:56,391
OK. EXistenZ.

434
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:59,432
Only from Antenna.

435
00:37:59,560 --> 00:38:02,028
- Here we go.
- You...

436
00:38:02,160 --> 00:38:04,594
You've got an unfair
advantage, don't you?

437
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:09,191
How can I possibly compete
with the designer of the system?

438
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:15,957
Well, you could beat the guy
that invented poker, couldn't you?

439
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,591
(Squealing)

440
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,911
(Electronic beeping)

441
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,550
(1st Man) That one?
(2nd Man) Yes.

442
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:43,989
(1st Man) Are you sure?
(2nd Man) Yes.

443
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:48,318
(1st Man) I wouldn't recommend it.
The graphics on this one are better.

444
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:53,355
(1st Man) This is the one you want.
(2nd Man) That one?

445
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:55,954
That was beautiful.

446
00:38:57,480 --> 00:38:59,232
(Electronic beeping)

447
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:05,675
I feel just like me.

448
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:08,228
Is that kind of transition normal?
That kinda...

449
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:15,111
smooth interlacing
from place to place?

450
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:16,872
It depends on the style of the game.

451
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,679
You can get jagged,
brutal cuts, slow fades,

452
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:22,320
shimmering little morphs.

453
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:27,475
This is amazing.

454
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:31,757
I had no idea.

455
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:37,674
Look at this.
Games I've never heard of.

456
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:41,395
Wait a minute. That reminds me.

457
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:46,235
What precisely is the goal
of the game that we're playing now?

458
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:49,311
You have to play the game

459
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:51,954
to find out why you're playing.

460
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:54,429
It's the future, Pikul.

461
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:57,630
You'll see how natural it feels.

462
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,953
Look at this.

463
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:31,991
Can this be the future?
Ever see anything like this?

464
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:37,319
These are delicate.
You got to be careful.

465
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:39,550
Yes, I can imagine.

466
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:43,150
Cortical Systematics
is the latest and the hottest.

467
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:46,397
Not just a new game,
but a new system.

468
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:49,631
Will it work with
an industry-standard bio-port?

469
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:53,670
I'm D'arcy Nader.

470
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:57,918
Welcome to D'arcy Nader's
Game Emporium.

471
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:01,595
Is there anything I can be,
oh, uh, helpin' you with?

472
00:41:01,680 --> 00:41:04,194
We're just looking.

473
00:41:09,440 --> 00:41:13,274
I have what you're lookin' for.

474
00:41:16,240 --> 00:41:18,708
Who sent you?

475
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:22,715
It's none of your business.

476
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:25,832
We're here. That's all that matters.

477
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:31,034
God. What happened?

478
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:35,872
I-I didn't mean to say that.

479
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,474
It's your character who said it.

480
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:42,832
Kind of a schizophrenic feeling,
isn't it? You'll get used to it.

