00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:09,792
- What's he doing?
- He's in a game loop.

487
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:15,000
He won't come out of it until you
give him some proper game dialogue.

488
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:20,115
Uh, this is tricky.

489
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,797
Repeat your last line.

490
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:27,714
Include his name
so he knows you're talking to him.

491
00:42:32,640 --> 00:42:37,191
We're here, D'arcy Nader,
and that's all that matters.

492
00:42:37,320 --> 00:42:39,117
Yes, you're right.

493
00:42:39,240 --> 00:42:42,152
That is all that matters.

494
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:49,517
Now, you said you have what we want.

495
00:42:49,640 --> 00:42:52,108
We're waiting.

496
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:55,437
You're going to need
these micro-pods

497
00:42:55,560 --> 00:42:58,711
to download your new identities.

498
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:01,872
I assume that you both
have had these

499
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:06,437
industry-standard bio-ports
that you mentioned installed.

500
00:43:07,440 --> 00:43:10,000
Yes, of course.
We both have bio-ports.

501
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:15,751
- We do, don't we?
- I assumed we did.

502
00:43:18,520 --> 00:43:20,909
In the game we might not.

503
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:23,195
We better check.

504
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:28,795
Yeah, it's there. Looks
a little different, but it's there.

505
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:34,673
Yeah, I see what you mean.

506
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:37,955
Yes, we both have bio-ports.

507
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:39,792
Good.

508
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:46,758
Port in, a-and this will tell ya
all you need to know...

509
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,751
for now.

510
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:52,196
I'm-I'm gonna leave
while you two, uh,

