finish up here, because, uh,

512
00:43:54,400 --> 00:43:58,518
it wouldn't be good
for us all to be seen together.

513
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:06,759
(Door closes)

514
00:44:07,840 --> 00:44:11,753
I assume that Nader
is our entry point into the game.

515
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:15,350
- Yeah. Kinda disappointing.
- Nader?

516
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:17,795
Yeah. He's not very well-drawn.

517
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:20,957
His dialogue was just so-so,
his accent...

518
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:25,472
Yeah.

519
00:44:32,400 --> 00:44:34,197
OK.

520
00:44:35,480 --> 00:44:37,675
Pods are so small.

521
00:44:37,760 --> 00:44:41,435
They plug directly
into the bio-port.

522
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:49,153
OK.

523
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:52,988
(Squishing)

524
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:54,479
- Oh God!
- What?

525
00:44:56,040 --> 00:45:00,477
The whole pod
just disappeared into your back.

526
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,551
It disappeared into my back?

527
00:45:02,640 --> 00:45:05,518
It's in my spine?!
It's around my spinal cord?!

528
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:07,273
It's just a game.

529
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:10,157
Do you feel anything yet?

530
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,718
No, I don't.

531
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:16,360
I don't feel a thing.

532
00:45:18,520 --> 00:45:21,273
- Want me to do you?
- Yeah.

533
00:45:57,480 --> 00:45:59,038
What the hell was that?

534
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:04,072
That wasn't me.
It was my game character.

535
00:46:04,160 --> 00:46:06,720
I wouldn't have done that.
Not here, anyway.

536
00:46:24,320 --> 00:46:27,835
Our characters are obviously
supposed to jump on each other.

537
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:30,354
It's most probably a...

538
00:46:32,040 --> 00:46:34,474
pathetically mechanical attempt...

539
00:46:34,560 --> 00:46:38,235
to heighten the emotional tension
of the next game sequence.

540
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:53,795
- No use fighting it, huh?
- What about... our new identities?

541
00:46:53,880 --> 00:46:56,314
Do you feel yours yet?

542
00:46:56,440 --> 00:46:58,476
They'll take care of themselves.

543
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:00,437
(Moaning)

544
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:08,513
I'm very worried about my body.

545
00:47:08,600 --> 00:47:10,955
(Gasping) Your what?

546
00:47:13,600 --> 00:47:15,556
Where are our real bodies?

547
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:20,350
Are they all right? What if they're
hungry? What if there's danger?

548
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:25,519
They're just where we left them.

549
00:47:25,600 --> 00:47:27,670
They're sitting quietly.

550
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:30,075
Eyes closed.

551
00:47:32,440 --> 00:47:36,069
It's, um, just like meditating.

552
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:43,877
I feel really vulnerable.

553
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:49,030
- Disembodied.
- OK.

554
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:55,195
Don't sweat it.

